<div class="page-section__sub-section">
	<h4>Flex Direction</h4>
	<p>The flex direction property tells the flex container on which direction to stack the flex item children. This property creates the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-flexbox-1/#main-axis" target="_blank">main axis</a> for the flex box. To stack them along the horizontal axis, use <code>.flex-row</code>, or <code>.flex-row-reverse</code> to reverse the stack order.</p>
	<div class="markup-panel flex-example">
		<div class="markup-panel__example">
<div class="d-flex flex-row">
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 1</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 2</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 3</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 4</div>
</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-row-reverse">
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 1</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 2</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 3</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 4</div>
</div>
		</div>
		<pre><code class="language-markup"></code></pre>
	</div>
	<p>To stack the flex items along the vertical axis, use <code>.flex-column</code>, or <code>.flex-column-reverse</code> to reverse the stack order.</p>
	<div class="markup-panel flex-example">
		<div class="markup-panel__example">
<div class="d-flex flex-column">
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 1</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 2</div>
</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-column-reverse">
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 1</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 2</div>
</div>
		</div>
		<pre><code class="language-markup"></code></pre>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="page-section__sub-section">
	<h4>Flex Wrap</h4>
	<p>The flex-wrap property tells the flex items whether they should fit into a single line or multiple lines. In order to wrap the flex items use <code>.flex-wrap</code>, or to reverse the wrap order, use <code>.flex-wrap-reverse</code></p>
	<div class="markup-panel flex-example">
		<div class="markup-panel__example">
<div class="d-flex flex-row flex-wrap">
	<div class="pad-xxs width-40">Flex Item 1</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs width-40">Flex Item 2</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs width-40">Flex Item 3</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs width-40">Flex Item 4</div>
</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-row flex-wrap-reverse">
	<div class="pad-xxs width-40">Flex Item 1</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs width-40">Flex Item 2</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs width-40">Flex Item 3</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs width-40">Flex Item 4</div>
</div>
		</div>
		<pre><code class="language-markup"></code></pre>
	</div>
	<p>In order to prevent wrapping, use <code>.flex-nowrap</code></p>
</div>
<div class="page-section__sub-section">
	<h4>Justify Content</h4>
	<p>The justify-content property tells the flex items how to align on the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-flexbox-1/#main-axis" target="_blank">main axis</a> of the flex box. For basic alignment, you can choose from <code>.justify-content-start</code>, <code>.justify-content-end</code> and <code>.justify-content-center</code>.</p>
	<div class="markup-panel flex-example">
		<div class="markup-panel__example">
<div class="d-flex flex-row justify-content-start">
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 1</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 2</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 3</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 4</div>
</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-row justify-content-end">
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 1</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 2</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 3</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 4</div>
</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-row justify-content-center">
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 1</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 2</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 3</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 4</div>
</div>
		</div>
		<pre><code class="language-markup"></code></pre>
	</div>
	<p>You can also space the flex items evenly across the flex box with <code>.justify-content-between</code> and <code>.justify-content-around</code>.</p>
	<div class="markup-panel flex-example">
