</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-row justify-content-around">
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 1</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 2</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 3</div>
	<div class="pad-xxs">Flex Item 4</div>
</div>
		</div>
		<pre><code class="language-markup"></code></pre>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="page-section__sub-section">
	<h4>Align Items</h4>
	<p>The align-items property tells the flex items how to align on the cross-axis, which is perpendicular to the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-flexbox-1/#main-axis" target="_blank">main axis</a> of the flex box. For basic alignment, you can choose from <code>.align-items-start</code>, <code>.align-items-end</code>, <code>.align-items-center</code> and <code>.align-items-baseline</code>.</p>
